Justice Abdul Hamid Yakubu of Gombe High Court 3 yesterday granted bail to a Facebook user, Bala Sanni, who was charged to court by the state government for posting “injurious contents” said to be capable of inciting and causing public disturbance in the state. Bala Sanni was arrested by the police in Abuja on March 17 and taken to Biliri correctional facility before he was charged to court two days later with  posting injurious falsehood and inciting public disturbance over an event that happened in October last year. Sanni was later relocated to Gombe correctional centre.   Two burnt to death in Anambra fire explosion     ‘Don’t exclude PWDs from election’     Navy rescues seven abducted in Rivers   He was granted bail at the Magistrate court with stringent conditions which he was unable to meet. His defence counsel, Haruna Lukas, filed a suit reapplying for bail and a review of the bail conditions. Justice Yakubu, while granting the application, asked Sanni to provide two sureties, one of whom a blood relation while the second must be someone of good standing in the society.